message.content: A 65-year-old African American male with a history of hypertension presents with urinary frequency, urgency, and nocturia, and elevated PSA levels, concerning for possible prostate cancer.

A 65-year-old African American male with a history of benign prostatic hyperplasia presents with urinary frequency, urgency, and nocturia, and is found to have an elevated PSA and abnormal digital rectal exam concerning for prostate cancer.

A 65-year-old African American male with a history of hypertension presents with complaints of urinary frequency and urgency, difficulty urinating, and blood in his urine, with a diagnosis of prostate cancer confirmed on biopsy.

A 65-year-old African American male with a history of benign prostatic hyperplasia presents with urinary symptoms and elevated prostate-specific antigen levels, ultimately diagnosed with prostate cancer.
